# LIMPIEZA DE DATOS MEJORADA
def clean_and_extract_text(comment):
    if pd.isna(comment):
        return ""

    text = str(comment)

    # 1. Estrategia robusta para traducciones de Google
    # Primero cortamos todo lo que venga despus de "(Original)" si existe
    if "(Original)" in text:
        text = text.split("(Original)")[0]

    # Luego eliminamos la etiqueta de inicio simplemente reemplazndola
    text = text.replace("(Translated by Google)", "")

    # 2. Limpieza de ruido en el texto
    text = re.sub(r'http\S+|www\S+|https\S+', '', text)  # Eliminar URLs
    text = re.sub(r'<.*?>', '', text)                    # Eliminar etiquetas HTML
    text = re.sub(r'\s+', ' ', text)                     # Normalizar espacios mltiples

    return text.strip()

# Aplicar limpieza y extraccin
df['review_text'] = df['comment'].apply(clean_and_extract_text)

# Crear versin en minsculas
df['review_clean'] = df['review_text'].str.lower()

# Filtrar reseas vacas
df = df[df['review_text'].str.len() > 0]

print(f" Limpieza completada y corregida: {len(df)} reseas vlidas.")

aspect_analysis = {}

for aspect, data in business_aspects.items():
    mentions = 0
    positive_mentions = 0
    negative_mentions = 0
    neutral_mentions = 0

    for idx, row in df.iterrows():
        text_lower = str(row['review_clean']) if pd.notna(row['review_clean']) else ""

        # Verificar si el aspecto es mencionado
        if any(keyword in text_lower for keyword in data['keywords']):
            mentions += 1

            # Verificar sentimiento especfico del aspecto
            has_positive = any(pos_phrase in text_lower for pos_phrase in data['positive'])
            has_negative = any(neg_phrase in text_lower for neg_phrase in data['negative'])

            if has_positive and not has_negative:
                positive_mentions += 1
            elif has_negative and not has_positive:
                negative_mentions += 1
            else:
                # Si no hay indicadores especficos, usar sentimiento general
                if row['expected_sentiment'] == 'positive':
                    positive_mentions += 0.5  # Peso reducido
                elif row['expected_sentiment'] == 'negative':
                    negative_mentions += 0.5
                else:
                    neutral_mentions += 1

    if mentions > 0:
        aspect_analysis[aspect] = {
            'total_mentions': mentions,
            'mention_rate': (mentions / len(df)) * 100,
            'positive_count': positive_mentions,
            'negative_count': negative_mentions,
            'neutral_count': neutral_mentions,
            'positive_rate': (positive_mentions / mentions) * 100 if mentions > 0 else 0,
            'negative_rate': (negative_mentions / mentions) * 100 if mentions > 0 else 0,
            'net_sentiment': ((positive_mentions - negative_mentions) / mentions) * 100 if mentions > 0 else 0
        }

# Ordenar por sentimiento neto
sorted_aspects = sorted(aspect_analysis.items(), key=lambda x: x[1]['net_sentiment'], reverse=True)

Anlisis con Modelos Avanzados

Modelo 1: Anlisis por Palabras Clave (Baseline)(Mtodo de Palabras Clave)

En esta etapa, se implement un mtodo de anlisis de sentimiento basado en listas de palabras. El sistema utiliza dos listas predefinidas: una con palabras de significado claramente positivo (como 'excelente' o 'increble') y otra con palabras claramente negativas (como 'terrible' o 'grosero').

La clasificacin funciona calculando un puntaje. Este se obtiene al contar las palabras positivas y negativas encontradas en el texto, y luego comparando su diferencia con respecto a la longitud total del comentario. Segn este puntaje, y usando un umbral bajo, el texto se etiqueta como positivo, negativo o neutral.

Para manejar casos donde no se encuentran palabras de las listas principales, se agregaron reglas simples. Estas reglas buscan trminos de neutralidad (como 'regular' o 'aceptable') y signos de exclamacin que puedan indicar nfasis.

Este modelo simple sirve como punto de partida para medir la mejora que ofrecen los modelos de aprendizaje automtico que se probarn despus. Su principal limitacin es que no comprende el contexto; por ejemplo, no detecta cuando una negacin cambia el sentido (como en "no es bueno") ni puede identificar sarcasmo.

# Diccionarios ampliados de palabras positivas y negativas
positive_words = set([
    'excellent', 'amazing', 'wonderful', 'fantastic', 'great', 'good', 'love', 'loved',
    'perfect', 'best', 'awesome', 'delicious', 'friendly', 'nice', 'recommend',
    'beautiful', 'clean', 'fresh', 'quality', 'tasty', 'cozy', 'comfortable',
    'spectacular', 'charming', 'lovely', 'pleasant', 'enjoyable', 'exceptional',
    'outstanding', 'superb', 'brilliant', 'fabulous', 'terrific', 'marvelous',
    'excellent', 'extraordinary', 'phenomenal', 'remarkable', 'splendid', 'magnificent'
])

negative_words = set([
    'bad', 'terrible', 'horrible', 'awful', 'worst', 'poor', 'disappointing',
    'rude', 'slow', 'cold', 'dirty', 'expensive', 'overpriced', 'never', 'avoid',
    'disgusting', 'unpleasant', 'mediocre', 'waste', 'noisy', 'uncomfortable',
    'disappointed', 'unfriendly', 'unprofessional', 'unhappy', 'dissatisfied',
    'pathetic', 'gross', 'nasty', 'dreadful', 'lousy', 'inferior', 'unacceptable',
    'appalling', 'atrocious', 'abysmal', 'horrendous', 'inadequate', 'substandard'
])

def keyword_sentiment_analysis(text):
    """Anlisis de sentimiento basado en palabras clave"""
    text_lower = str(text).lower()
    words = text_lower.split()

    pos_count = sum(1 for word in words if word in positive_words)
    neg_count = sum(1 for word in words if word in negative_words)

    # Intensificadores
    if 'very' in words or 'really' in words or 'extremely' in words:
        pos_count *= 1.5
        neg_count *= 1.5

    # Negacin
    if 'not' in words or "n't" in text_lower:
        pos_count, neg_count = neg_count * 0.5, pos_count * 0.5

    # Clasificacin
    total_sentiment = pos_count - neg_count

    if total_sentiment > 1:
        return 'positive'
    elif total_sentiment < -1:
        return 'negative'
    else:
        return 'neutral'

# Aplicar anlisis
df['keyword_sentiment'] = df['review_text'].apply(keyword_sentiment_analysis)

print(" Anlisis por palabras clave completado")

# Inicializar VADER
sia = SentimentIntensityAnalyzer()

def vader_sentiment_analysis(text):
    """Anlisis con VADER - especializado en redes sociales"""
    scores = sia.polarity_scores(text)

    # VADER devuelve compound score entre -1 y 1
    if scores['compound'] >= 0.05:
        return 'positive'
    elif scores['compound'] <= -0.05:
        return 'negative'
    else:
        return 'neutral'

# Aplicar VADER
print(" Analizando con VADER...")

def textblob_sentiment_analysis(text):
    """Anlisis con TextBlob"""
    try:
        blob = TextBlob(str(text))
        polarity = blob.sentiment.polarity

        if polarity > 0.1:
            return 'positive'
        elif polarity < -0.1:
            return 'negative'
        else:
            return 'neutral'
    except:
        return 'neutral'

# Aplicar TextBlob
print(" Analizando con TextBlob...")

print(" Cargando modelo spaCy...")
try:
    # Intentamos el modelo transformer si est instalado
    nlp = spacy.load("en_core_web_trf")
    print(" Usando modelo transformer (RoBERTa)")
except:
    # Si no, usamos el modelo small (ms rpido para 1665 reseas)
    nlp = spacy.load("en_core_web_sm")
    print(" Usando modelo small")

def spacy_sentiment_analysis(text):
    """Anlisis con spaCy basado en polaridad de palabras y entidades"""
    if not text:
        return 'neutral'

    doc = nlp(text[:1000])  # Mantenemos el lmite de caracteres por doc para evitar cuelgues

    pos_score = 0
    neg_score = 0

    # Anlisis por tokens (usando los diccionarios unificados de pasos anteriores)
    for token in doc:
        token_lower = token.text.lower()
        if token_lower in positive_words:
            pos_score += 1
        elif token_lower in negative_words:
            neg_score += 1

    # Anlisis de contexto de entidades (Lugares/Productos)
    for ent in doc.ents:
        if ent.label_ in ['ORG', 'PRODUCT', 'GPE']:
            context = text[max(0, ent.start_char-20):min(len(text), ent.end_char+20)].lower()
            if any(word in context for word in ['great', 'excellent', 'best', 'good']):
                pos_score += 0.5
            elif any(word in context for word in ['terrible', 'worst', 'awful', 'bad']):
                neg_score += 0.5

    # Clasificacin final
    if pos_score > neg_score + 1:
        return 'positive'
    elif neg_score > pos_score + 1:
        return 'negative'
    else:
        return 'neutral'

print(" Cargando modelo BERT...")

# 1. Configuracin del dispositivo (GPU si est disponible)
device = 0 if torch.cuda.is_available() else -1
print(f"Usando: {' GPU' if device == 0 else ' CPU'}")

model_name = "nlptown/bert-base-multilingual-uncased-sentiment"

try:
    classifier = pipeline(
        "sentiment-analysis",
        model=model_name,
        device=device
    )

    # 2. Preparar los datos
    texts = df['review_text'].str[:512].tolist() # BERT tiene lmite de 512 tokens
    total_reviews = len(texts)

    # 3. Procesamiento en lotes para eficiencia
    batch_size = 16
    bert_sentiments = []

    print(f" Analizando {total_reviews} reseas con BERT...")

    for i in range(0, total_reviews, batch_size):
        batch = texts[i : i + batch_size]

        try:
            results = classifier(batch)
            for result in results:
                label = result['label']
                # Mapeo de 1-5 estrellas a sentimiento textual
                if label in ['1 star', '2 stars']:
                    bert_sentiments.append('negative')
                elif label == '3 stars':
                    bert_sentiments.append('neutral')
                else:  # 4 o 5 stars
                    bert_sentiments.append('positive')
        except Exception as e:
            # En caso de error en un lote especfico, llenamos con neutral
            bert_sentiments.extend(['neutral'] * len(batch))

        # Reporte de progreso cada 200 reseas
        if (i + batch_size) % 200 == 0 or (i + batch_size) >= total_reviews:
            print(f"    Procesadas {min(i + batch_size, total_reviews)}/{total_reviews} reseas...")

    # 4. Asignar resultados al DataFrame original
    df['sentiment_bert'] = bert_sentiments

    print(f"\n Anlisis BERT completado para {len(df)} reseas")
    print(f" Distribucin BERT:")
    print(df['sentiment_bert'].value_counts())

    BERT_AVAILABLE = True

except Exception as e:
    print(f" Error con BERT: {e}")
    BERT_AVAILABLE = False

# ==============================================================================
# FASE 1: PREPROCESAMIENTO
# ==============================================================================

lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()
stop_words = set(stopwords.words('english'))

# Stopwords personalizadas (Mnimas para no borrar info valiosa)
custom_stops = {
    'really', 'very', 'go', 'get', 'also', 'would', 'could', 'should',
    'make', 'much', 'even', 'place', 'restaurant'
}
stop_words.update(custom_stops)

# Descarga adicional de NLTK para punkt_tab y averaged_perceptron_tagger
nltk.download('punkt_tab', quiet=True)
nltk.download('averaged_perceptron_tagger_eng', quiet=True)

def clean_text_advanced(text):
    if pd.isna(text) or text is None: return ""
    text = str(text).lower()
    text = re.sub(r'http\S+|www\S+|https\S+', '', text) # URLs
    text = re.sub(r'\S+@\S+', '', text) # Emails
    text = re.sub(r'[^a-z\s\']', ' ', text) # Solo letras y apostrofes
    text = re.sub(r'\s+', ' ', text).strip() # Espacios
    return text

def filter_by_pos(text):
    """Filtra manteniendo sustantivos, adjetivos, verbos y adverbios"""
    if not text: return ""
    keep_pos = ['NN', 'NNS', 'NNP', 'NNPS', 'JJ', 'JJR', 'JJS', 'VB', 'VBG', 'RB']

    tokens = word_tokenize(text)
    pos_tags = nltk.pos_tag(tokens)

    filtered = [
        lemmatizer.lemmatize(word)
        for word, pos in pos_tags
        if pos in keep_pos and word not in stop_words and len(word) > 1
    ]
    return " ".join(filtered)

print("Limpiando y procesando textos...")

# Aplicamos al dataframe existente
# Usamos tu columna 'review_text' como base (que ya limpiamos de traducciones antes)
df['text_clean_base'] = df['review_text'].apply(clean_text_advanced)
df['text_for_bertopic_pos'] = df['text_clean_base'].apply(filter_by_pos)

# Filtramos las que hayan quedado vacas
df_topics = df[df['text_for_bertopic_pos'].str.len() > 2].copy()
print(f" Textos procesados. Reseas listas: {len(df_topics)}")

# ==============================================================================
# FASE 2: CLASIFICACIN POR CATEGORAS (Zero-Shot)
# ==============================================================================

categories = [
    "coffee quality",
    "food quality",
    "service and staff",
    "atmosphere and ambiance",
    "location and accessibility",
    "price and value"
]

print(" Cargando modelo de clasificacin (puede tardar)...")
# Usamos GPU si est disponible
device = 0 if torch.cuda.is_available() else -1

classifier = pipeline(
    "zero-shot-classification",
    model="microsoft/deberta-v2-xlarge-mnli",
    # Si falla por memoria, usa: "valhalla/distilbart-mnli-12-3"
    device=device
)

def batch_classify_reviews(texts, batch_size=8, threshold=0.5): # Batch ms pequeo por seguridad
    all_categories = []

    for i in tqdm(range(0, len(texts), batch_size), desc="Clasificando"):
        batch = texts[i:i+batch_size]
        batch_results = [[] for _ in range(len(batch))]

        valid_indices = [j for j, t in enumerate(batch) if len(str(t).strip()) > 3]
        valid_batch = [batch[j] for j in valid_indices]

        if not valid_batch:
            all_categories.extend(batch_results)
            continue

        try:
            results = classifier(
                valid_batch,
                categories,
                multi_label=True,
                hypothesis_template="This review discusses {}."
            )

            if not isinstance(results, list): results = [results]

            for idx, res in zip(valid_indices, results):
                cats = [label for label, score in zip(res['labels'], res['scores']) if score >= threshold]
                batch_results[idx] = cats

        except Exception as e:
            print(f"Error en batch {i}: {e}")

        all_categories.extend(batch_results)

    return all_categories

# Ejecutar clasificacin
print(" Clasificando reseas")
# Usamos un umbral de 0.85 para que solo clasifique si est muy seguro
df_topics['categories'] = batch_classify_reviews(
    df_topics['text_clean_base'].tolist(),
    batch_size=8,
    threshold=0.85
)

# Verificacin rpida
for cat in categories:
    count = df_topics['categories'].apply(lambda x: cat in x).sum()
    print(f"  -> {cat}: {count} reseas")

# ==============================================================================
# FASE 3 MEJORADA: BERTopic CON LIMPIEZA CONTEXTUAL
# ==============================================================================

# 1. Configuracin de Stopwords Inteligentes
# Quitamos la palabra obvia de cada categora para ver los detalles reales
category_stopwords = {
    "coffee quality": ["coffee", "cafe", "cup", "drink", "flavor"],
    "food quality": ["food", "eat", "meal", "dish", "menu"],
    "service and staff": ["service", "staff", "waiter", "waitress", "people", "attention"],
    "price and value": ["price", "money", "value", "expensive", "cheap", "cost"],
    "atmosphere and ambiance": ["atmosphere", "place", "spot", "ambiance", "vibe", "decor"],
    "location and accessibility": ["location", "place", "near", "area"]
}

# Stopwords base + ruido genrico ("excellent excellent")
base_stopwords = list(stopwords.words('english'))
generic_noise = ["good", "great", "nice", "excellent", "amazing", "really", "very", "best", "bad"]

# Diccionarios para guardar resultados
all_topics_detailed = {}
category_insights = {}

print(" Iniciando anlisis de tpicos REFINADO...")

for category in categories:
    print(f"\n--- {category.upper()} ---")

    # 2. Filtrar reseas de esta categora
    cat_reviews = df_topics[df_topics['categories'].apply(lambda x: category in x)]

    if len(cat_reviews) < 10:
        print(f" Saltando: pocas reseas especficas ({len(cat_reviews)}).")
        category_insights[category] = {'keywords': []}
        continue

    print(f"  -> Analizando {len(cat_reviews)} reseas especficas.")

    # 3. Configurar Vectorizer NICO para esta categora
    # Unimos: base + ruido genrico + palabras obvias de ESTA categora
    current_stopwords = base_stopwords + generic_noise + category_stopwords.get(category, [])

    vectorizer_model = CountVectorizer(
        stop_words=current_stopwords,
        min_df=2,
        ngram_range=(1, 2)
    )

    # 4. Entrenar BERTopic
    topic_model = BERTopic(
        embedding_model="all-MiniLM-L6-v2",
        vectorizer_model=vectorizer_model,
        nr_topics="auto",
        min_topic_size=3,
        verbose=False
    )

    try:
        texts = cat_reviews['text_for_bertopic_pos'].tolist()
        topics, probs = topic_model.fit_transform(texts)

        # 5. Guardar y mostrar resultados limpios
        freq = topic_model.get_topic_info()
        freq = freq[freq['Topic'] != -1]

        # Guardar para insights
        all_keywords_list = []
        cat_topics_data = []

        for idx, row in freq.iterrows():
            topic_id = row['Topic']
            # Extraer palabras
            words = [w[0] for w in topic_model.get_topic(topic_id)]
            all_keywords_list.extend(words)

            # Guardar datos del tpico
            cat_topics_data.append({
                'topic_id': topic_id,
                'count': row['Count'],
                'keywords': ", ".join(words[:7])
            })

            # Mostrar solo los 3 primeros tpicos para no saturar pantalla
            if idx < 3:
                print(f"   Tpico {topic_id}: {', '.join(words[:5])}")

        category_insights[category] = {'keywords': list(set(all_keywords_list))}
        all_topics_detailed[category] = pd.DataFrame(cat_topics_data)

    except Exception as e:
        print(f"   No se pudieron generar tpicos: {e}")
        category_insights[category] = {'keywords': []}

print("\n Anlisis completado con filtros de calidad.")

# ==============================================================================
# FASE 4 MEJORADA: GENERACIN DE INSIGHTS (Filtrado Inteligente)
# ==============================================================================

mask_filler = pipeline("fill-mask", model="bert-base-uncased", device=device)

# 1. Templates DESCRIPTIVOS (Evitan consejos locos como "hazlo ms caro")
sentence_templates = {
    'coffee quality': [
        "Reviewers say the coffee taste is [MASK].",  # Sabor
        "The coffee is described as [MASK]."           # Descripcin general
    ],
    'food quality': [
        "Customers mention the food is [MASK].",
        "The food quality is considered [MASK]."
    ],
    'service and staff': [
        "The staff is described as [MASK].",
        "The service provided is [MASK]."
    ],
    'atmosphere and ambiance': [
        "The atmosphere is [MASK].",
        "The place feels [MASK]."
    ],
    'price and value': [
        "Customers describe the prices as [MASK].",   # Aqu s queremos saber si es caro
        "The value for money is [MASK]."
    ],
    'location and accessibility': [
        "The location is [MASK].",
        "Getting to the place is [MASK]."
    ]
}

# 2. Blacklist de palabras "intiles" o confusas para insights
# Eliminamos palabras que gramaticalmente encajan pero no dicen nada til
ignore_words = {
    "normal", "important", "rich", "smooth", "well", "also", "much", "even",
    "coffee", "food", "place", "thing", "something", "really", "very",
    "expensive", "cheap", "high", "low" # Quitamos precio de otras categoras
}

# Solo permitimos "expensive/cheap/high/low" en la categora de PRECIO
price_keywords = {"expensive", "cheap", "reasonable", "high", "low", "fair", "good"}

def generate_insights(template, candidate_keywords, category):
    if not candidate_keywords: return []

    try:
        # Pedimos muchas opciones para filtrar despus
        preds = mask_filler(template, top_k=150)
    except:
        return []

    valid_insights = []
    keywords_lower = set([k.lower() for k in candidate_keywords])

    for pred in preds:
        token = pred['token_str'].strip().lower()

        # FILTROS DE CALIDAD:
        # 1. Debe ser una palabra detectada en los tpicos
        if token not in keywords_lower: continue

        # 2. No debe ser una palabra ignorada (salvo excepciones de precio)
        if category != 'price and value' and token in ignore_words: continue

        # 3. Debe tener longitud suficiente
        if len(token) < 3: continue

        # 4. Si es categora precio, solo aceptamos adjetivos de precio
        if category == 'price and value' and token not in price_keywords:
             # A veces "delicious" se cuela en precio, lo evitamos
             continue

        # Formato de salida limpio
        valid_insights.append(f"{pred['sequence']} (Confianza: {pred['score']:.1%})")
        if len(valid_insights) >= 3: break

    return valid_insights

print("\n==========================================")
print(" REPORT DE PERCEPCIN DEL CLIENTE (Final)")
print("==========================================\n")

for category, data in category_insights.items():
    if not data.get('keywords'): continue

    print(f" {category.upper()}")
    # Mostramos keywords base para entender de dnde saca la info
    print(f"   (Keywords base: {', '.join(data['keywords'][:5])}...)")

    templates = sentence_templates.get(category, [])
    for tmpl in templates:
        suggestions = generate_insights(tmpl, data['keywords'], category)
        if suggestions:
            print(f"   {tmpl}")
            for s in suggestions:
                print(f"      {s}")
    print("-" * 40)

# VISUALIZACIONES BERTOPIC - ANLISIS INTERACTIVO DE TPICOS

print(" Generando visualizaciones BERTopic para anlisis profundo...")
print("="*70)

# Diccionario para almacenar modelos de cada categora
category_models = {}
category_visualizations = {}

# Re-entrenar modelos si es necesario para generar visualizaciones
for category in categories:
    print(f"\n Procesando visualizaciones para: {category.upper()}")

    # Filtrar reseas de esta categora
    cat_reviews = df_topics[df_topics['categories'].apply(lambda x: category in x)]

    if len(cat_reviews) < 10:
        print(f" Saltando: muy pocas reseas ({len(cat_reviews)})")
        continue

    # Configurar stopwords especficas
    current_stopwords = base_stopwords + generic_noise + category_stopwords.get(category, [])

    vectorizer_model = CountVectorizer(
        stop_words=current_stopwords,
        min_df=2,
        ngram_range=(1, 2)
    )

    # Crear modelo BERTopic
    topic_model = BERTopic(
        embedding_model="all-MiniLM-L6-v2",
        vectorizer_model=vectorizer_model,
        nr_topics="auto",
        min_topic_size=5,
        verbose=False
    )

    try:
        texts = cat_reviews['text_for_bertopic_pos'].tolist()
        topics, probs = topic_model.fit_transform(texts)

        # Guardar el modelo
        category_models[category] = {
            'model': topic_model,
            'topics': topics,
            'probs': probs,
            'texts': texts
        }

        print(f"  Modelo listo para visualizacin ({len(set(topics))-1} tpicos encontrados)")

    except Exception as e:
        print(f"  Error al crear modelo para visualizacin: {e}")

print("\n Modelos preparados para visualizacin interactiva")

summary_stats = []
for category, model_data in category_models.items():
    if model_data:
        topics = model_data['topics']
        topic_model = model_data['model']

        # Calcular estadsticas
        n_topics = len(set(topics)) - 1  # Excluir -1 (outliers)
        n_outliers = (np.array(topics) == -1).sum()
        total_docs = len(topics)
        outlier_rate = (n_outliers / total_docs) * 100

        # Obtener el tpico ms grande
        topic_info = topic_model.get_topic_info()
        if not topic_info.empty:
            largest_topic = topic_info[topic_info['Topic'] != -1].iloc[0]
            largest_topic_size = largest_topic['Count']
            largest_topic_pct = (largest_topic_size / total_docs) * 100
        else:
            largest_topic_size = 0
            largest_topic_pct = 0

        summary_stats.append({
            'Categora': category.upper(),
            'Total Docs': total_docs,
            'Nm. Tpicos': n_topics,
            'Outliers': f'{n_outliers} ({outlier_rate:.1f}%)',
            'Tpico Mayor': f'{largest_topic_size} ({largest_topic_pct:.1f}%)'
        })

# Crear DataFrame con estadsticas

            total = len(topics)
            coherence = 100 - (n_outliers / total * 100)  # Inverso de outliers
            coherence_scores.append(coherence)

    # Grfico de radar/polar para coherencia
    angles = np.linspace(0, 2 * np.pi, len(categories_list), endpoint=False).tolist()
    coherence_scores = coherence_scores + coherence_scores[:1]  # Cerrar el crculo
    angles += angles[:1]

    ax2 = plt.subplot(122, projection='polar')
    ax2.plot(angles, coherence_scores, 'o-', linewidth=2, color='#FF6B6B')
    ax2.fill(angles, coherence_scores, alpha=0.25, color='#FF6B6B')
    ax2.set_xticks(angles[:-1])
    ax2.set_xticklabels(categories_list, size=10)
    ax2.set_ylim(0, 100)

def calculate_metrics(y_true, y_pred, model_name):
    """Calcula todas las mtricas de evaluacin para un modelo"""

    # Filtrar NaN si existen
    mask = ~(pd.isna(y_true) | pd.isna(y_pred))
    y_true = y_true[mask]
    y_pred = y_pred[mask]

    # Mtricas bsicas
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_true, y_pred)
    precision = precision_score(y_true, y_pred, average='weighted', zero_division=0)
    recall = recall_score(y_true, y_pred, average='weighted', zero_division=0)
    f1 = f1_score(y_true, y_pred, average='weighted', zero_division=0)
    kappa = cohen_kappa_score(y_true, y_pred)

    # Mtricas por clase
    precision_per_class = precision_score(y_true, y_pred, average=None, labels=['positive', 'neutral', 'negative'], zero_division=0)
    recall_per_class = recall_score(y_true, y_pred, average=None, labels=['positive', 'neutral', 'negative'], zero_division=0)
    f1_per_class = f1_score(y_true, y_pred, average=None, labels=['positive', 'neutral', 'negative'], zero_division=0)

    return {
        'model': model_name,
        'accuracy': accuracy,
        'precision': precision,
        'recall': recall,
        'f1_score': f1,
        'kappa': kappa,
        'precision_positive': precision_per_class[0],
        'precision_neutral': precision_per_class[1],
        'precision_negative': precision_per_class[2],
        'recall_positive': recall_per_class[0],
        'recall_neutral': recall_per_class[1],
        'recall_negative': recall_per_class[2],
        'f1_positive': f1_per_class[0],
        'f1_neutral': f1_per_class[1],
        'f1_negative': f1_per_class[2]
    }

# Primero, aseguramos de que 'true_sentiment' existe (basado en estrellas)
star_to_sentiment = {
    'ONE': 'negative', 'TWO': 'negative',
    'THREE': 'neutral',
    'FOUR': 'positive', 'FIVE': 'positive'
}
if 'starRating' in df.columns:
    df['true_sentiment'] = df['starRating'].map(star_to_sentiment)

print(" Calculando mtricas de evaluacin...\n")

metrics_results = []

# Definimos un diccionario con: {Nombre para la tabla: Nombre real de la columna en df}
modelos_a_evaluar = {
    'Palabras Clave': 'keyword_sentiment',
    'VADER': 'vader_sentiment',
    'TextBlob': 'textblob_sentiment',
    'spaCy': 'sentiment_spacy',
    'BERT': 'sentiment_bert'
}

for label, col_name in modelos_a_evaluar.items():

        # Solo calculamos si la columna existe en el DataFrame

    else:

# Crear DataFrame con mtricas
if metrics_results:

    # Mostrar mtricas por clase
    print("\n MTRICAS POR CLASE (F1-Score)")
    print("="*80)
    print(metrics_df[['model', 'f1_positive', 'f1_neutral', 'f1_negative']].to_string(index=False))
else:
    print(" No se encontraron columnas de resultados de modelos para evaluar.")

# Add Keyword sentiment
if 'keyword_sentiment' in df.columns:
    models.append(('Palabras Clave', df['keyword_sentiment'], df['true_sentiment']))

# Add VADER sentiment
if 'vader_sentiment' in df.columns:
    models.append(('VADER', df['vader_sentiment'], df['true_sentiment']))

# Add TextBlob sentiment
if 'textblob_sentiment' in df.columns:
    models.append(('TextBlob', df['textblob_sentiment'], df['true_sentiment']))

# Add spaCy sentiment
if 'sentiment_spacy' in df.columns:
    models.append(('spaCy', df['sentiment_spacy'], df['true_sentiment']))

# Add BERT sentiment
if 'sentiment_bert' in df.columns and BERT_AVAILABLE:
    models.append(('BERT', df['sentiment_bert'], df['true_sentiment']))

# Llenar con grfico vaco si no hay suficientes modelos (mx 6 plots)
while len(models) < 6:
    models.append(('', None, None))

labels = ['positive', 'neutral', 'negative']

for idx, (model_name, y_pred, y_true) in enumerate(models):
    ax = axes[idx // 3, idx % 3]

    if y_pred is not None and y_true is not None:
        # Filtrar NaN
        mask = ~(pd.isna(y_true) | pd.isna(y_pred))
        y_true_clean = y_true[mask]
        y_pred_clean = y_pred[mask]

        cm = confusion_matrix(y_true_clean, y_pred_clean, labels=labels)

        # Visualizar
        sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues',
                   xticklabels=labels, yticklabels=labels, ax=ax)
        ax.set_title(f'{model_name}')
        ax.set_ylabel('Verdadero')
        ax.set_xlabel('Predicho')
    else:
        ax.axis('off') # Turn off axis for empty plots

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
